args:
The prince and his friends are saved by an enka
singer called Marvelous Naoto who proposes a
bon dance in order to mend fences. But when
Catherine and Eugene begin the dance, fiends
close in, forcing the prince to face off against
them in order to keep the dance going.
Looks like we managed to shake them.\nThanks for the help, stranger.
When one dragon shuts the door,\na singer will appear to open it.
By my curls, it's you! You'reâ€”
IT'S MARVELOUS NAOTO!\nWhy are you in our town?!
He's one of the leading enka singers in\nall of Hinomoto. I invited him here as a\nsecret festival guest.
Can I have an autograph, Mr. Marvelous?\nI'm your BIGGEST fan.
An extremely delightful and auspicious\noccasion this is! Nevertheless, I suspect\nit to also be a critical moment.
Yeah, so here's what's going on...

You are heard. It appears the flame
burning at the heart of this event most
strange is trouble between the young
man and woman here.
But we don't know how to reconcileâ€”\nI mean, REALLY reconcile. From the\nbottom of our hearts and all that.
Once swallowed up in the eddies of\npassion, the many become as one.
To be lost in a fever dream is to see\none's heart open in due course.
I'm having a marvelously impossible time\nfollowing a dang thing you're saying.
The fool with worry in their heart ought\njust dance. Round and round the stage\nthey go! Spin, spin, spin!
Um, are you saying we should\nhold a bon dance?
Of course! Dancing always leads\nto a happy ending!
...In my DREAMS! Come now, if this\ncould be solved with a few simple\ntwirls, we'd have done so already!
What I suggest is no more than\na bon dance. But also, no less.
Would you please just answer my\ndarling's question like a normal person?!
When you and me were slugging it out,\nSam's dance calmed us down, remember?
So if we dance a bon dance together,\nit'll make Sam and the Styxes happy.
What sort of mad logic is that?!
Hey, if you have a better idea, I'm all ears.\nBut I don't think you doâ€”so let's dance.
Rrrr! Fineâ€”but only because I can't\ncome up with a less-absurd option.
Let's hurry to the festival stage.
I shall perform the lead. Young man?\nYoung lady? YOU...shall dance.
You say that, but I haven't done a\nbon dance since I was a little kid.
Then permit me to assist you.\nFollow my lead and move as I do.
All who live, gather in the circle\nand dance! Let the music play!
Eugene, you're not following the beat!\nAlso, you must keep your hand like this.
I'm trying! You're just moving too fast!
The point of all this is NOT for\nyou two to start fighting again!
Er, yes. Of course. In that case, I will\ndance a little more slowly so you can\nmore easily follow my movements...
And I'll put more strength in my arms\nand legs so I can follow along...
They're even breathing in sync!\nBut wait, what's...?
It's the Styxesâ€”but there's something\ndifferent about them.
They were trying to burn this place to\nthe ground a second ago, but now\nthey're just dancing and having fun.
The eddies of passion enfold us all.\nEven dragons move to rapture's gambol.
I actually think this is going to work...
Affected by the passion, the fiends roil.\nThey make for the stage with the swift\nfootfalls of the hastened runner.
Yet that would lack in charm. If fiends\nrage and turn this to an offering of\nblood, all will come to nothing.
We'll take care of the fiendsâ€”\nyou just finish the dance.
You are heard. Do not be even\na little careless, seventh scion.
